<article xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" specific-use="sps-1.4" dtd-version="1.0" xml:lang="pt" article-type="research-article"><front><journal-meta><journal-id journal-id-type="publisher-id">rbcpol</journal-id><journal-title-group><journal-title>Revista Brasileira de Ciência Política</journal-title><abbrev-journal-title abbrev-type="publisher">Rev. Bras. Ciênc. Polít.</abbrev-journal-title></journal-title-group><issn pub-type="ppub">0103-3352</issn><issn pub-type="epub">2178-4884</issn><publisher><publisher-name>Universidade de Brasília. Instituto de Ciência Política</publisher-name><publisher-loc>Brasília, DF, Brazil</publisher-loc></publisher></journal-meta><article-meta><article-id pub-id-type="publisher-id" specific-use="scielo-v2">S0103-33522024000100214</article-id><article-id pub-id-type="publisher-id" specific-use="scielo-v1">S0103-3352(24)04300000214</article-id><article-id pub-id-type="doi">10.1590/0103-3352.2024.43.275111</article-id><article-categories><subj-group subj-group-type="heading"><subject>Artigo Original</subject></subj-group></article-categories><title-group><article-title>Entre o fortalecimento institucional e tendências de precarização da força de trabalho: orçamento e emprego público no Poder Judiciário (1986-2021)</article-title><trans-title-group xml:lang="en"><trans-title>Between institutional strengthening and workforce deterioration: budgets and public employment in the judiciary (1986-2021)</trans-title></trans-title-group></title-group><contrib-group><contrib contrib-type="author"><contrib-id contrib-id-type="orcid">0000-0001-9825-6968</contrib-id><name><surname>Pacheco</surname><given-names>João Pedro</given-names></name><xref ref-type="aff" rid="aff2"/></contrib></contrib-group><aff id="aff2"><addr-line><named-content content-type="city">Picos</named-content><named-content content-type="state">Piauí</named-content></addr-line><institution content-type="orgname">Universidade Estadual do Piauí</institution><country country="BR">Brazil</country><email>joaochaves.pcs@uespi.br</email></aff><pub-date pub-type="epub-ppub"><year>2024</year></pub-date><volume>43</volume><elocation-id>e275111</elocation-id><history><date date-type="received"><day>25</day><month>05</month><year>2023</year></date><date date-type="accepted"><day>12</day><month>07</month><year>2024</year></date></history><permissions><license license-type="open-access" xlink:href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" xml:lang="en"><license-p>This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License.</license-p></license></permissions><abstract><p>Resumo: Neste trabalho, trato da reestruturação institucional do Poder Judiciário no Brasil desde a volta à democracia. Para tanto, analiso como tem sido a gestão de suas despesas e de sua força de trabalho nas últimas três décadas. Os resultados apontam que, com o fim do período autoritário, o Judiciário recuperou sua autonomia e independência, o que resultou em seu fortalecimento institucional, evidenciado no incremento orçamentário e no aumento e modernização de sua força de trabalho. Entretanto, na última década, apesar de ganhos financeiros acima da inflação, tem havido redução em seu quadro de pessoal efetivo e crescimento de força de trabalho sem vínculo. Tal fato indica que, possivelmente, esteja havendo uma precarização da força de trabalho do Poder Judiciário no Brasil.</p></abstract><trans-abstract xml:lang="en"><p>Abstract: In this article, I examine the institutional restructuring of the judicial branch of government in Brazil since the return to democracy. I analyze the management of judicial expenses and workforce over the last three decades. The results indicate that, with the end of the authoritarian period, the judicial branch recovered its autonomy and independence, which resulted in institutional strengthening, evidenced in an increased budget and in an expanding and modernized workforce. However, in the last decade, despite financial gains above inflation, the permanent staff of the judiciary has declined, as has the growth of the non-contractual workforce. This fact is suggestive of a possible deterioration of the workforce of the Judiciary in Brazil.</p></trans-abstract><kwd-group xml:lang="pt" kwd-group-type="author-generated"><kwd>orçamento público</kwd><kwd>emprego público</kwd><kwd>poder judiciário</kwd><kwd>precarização</kwd><kwd>terceirização</kwd></kwd-group><kwd-group xml:lang="en" kwd-group-type="author-generated"><kwd>government budget</kwd><kwd>public employment</kwd><kwd>judiciary</kwd><kwd>precariousness</kwd><kwd>outsourcing</kwd></kwd-group><counts><fig-count count="0"/><table-count count="0"/><equation-count count="0"/><ref-count count="27"/><page-count count="0"/></counts></article-meta></front><back><ref-list><ref id="B1"><element-citation publication-type="book"><source>Ministério Público e política no Brasil</source><date><year>2002</year></date><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>ARANTES</surname><given-names>R.</given-names></name></person-group></element-citation></ref><ref id="B2"><element-citation publication-type="journal"><article-title>Revisionismo histórico e ideologia: as diferentes fases da política econômica dos governos do PT</article-title><source>Brazilian Keynesian Review</source><date><year>2018</year></date><fpage>102</fpage><lpage>115</lpage><issue>1</issue><volume>4</volume><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>BARBOSA</surname><given-names>Nelson</given-names></name></person-group><comment>[s.l.]</comment></element-citation></ref><ref id="B3"><element-citation publication-type="book"><source>Profissionalismo e política no mundo do Direito</source><date><year>2002</year></date><volume>1</volume><person-group person-group-type="author"><name><surname>BONELLI</surname><given-names>M. G.</given-names></name></person-group></element-citation></ref><ref id="B4"><element-citation publication-type="book"><source>Orçamen